<TITLE> 10 die in Bandarban hill slides </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, July 31 (bdnews24.com)At least 10 people, six of a family, died in multiple hill collapses early on Friday in Aziznagar in Lama upazila of Bandarban. Torrential rains triggered the landslide in three places at around 3am, police and locals said. Abul Hossain, 60, his mother Gulzar Begum, 100, wife Amina Khatun, 51, son Md Yunus, 17, daughter Setara Bibi, 19 and grandson Omar Faruque, 11 were victims of a seven-member family of Aziznagar. The survivor of the family was not in the house at the time of the occurrence. The other victims were Mohammad Alamgir, son of Mohammad Ibrahim from Sandwippara, 'Rifat-, 3, son of Shawkat Alam, 'Rehana', 11, from Telunia and 'Ferdaus', 4, from Gazaliapara. Rehana had travelled to her sister's home from Chunuti of Lohagara Upazila in Chittagong. Another 35-year-old unidentified person died in a similar incident in Gazaria under Lama upazila. Local journalists said neighbours had recovered some of the bodies from Harinmara Parah while fire service men of Satkania in Chittagong and Chakaria in Cox's Bazar recovered the rest of the bodies at around 2pm. Chakaria fire service station official Mohammad Mostafa Khan told bdnews24.com that Jahangir Alam, 22, injured from hill slide, had been admitted to a local hospital. The bodies were handed to relatives in presence of the police, he added. Bandarban police chief Quamrul Ahsan said that the victims had been sleeping in bamboo-made houses at the bottom of the hills. At least 130 people died in a landslide in Chittagong in June, 2007. bdnews2
